@NODE N7 "History"

v2.1 (6/4/1998)

  - Added  some  text to window titlebar to show which line  you
    are currently on and how many lines the textfile being ARead
    contains.    Currently  this  feature  is  implemented  with
    SetWindowTitles().  Suggested by Jon Aslund.

  - Changed  MAXLINES  to 9999.  This is really just to save  an
    extra  div instruction when ARead is generating text for the
    window titlebar.

  - Got round to changing the way ARead handles CLI input.   Now
    CLI  args  have 1 char equivilents (N=Name/A, P=PUBSCREEN/S,
    etc).  Suggested by that lazy typer Nils Goers :^)

  - Fixed BIG memory leak problem!  I only found this BUG  while
    optimizing  the  AllocVec functions  in ARead, I'm supprised
    nobody  (incl  me)  noticed the 64KB+ memory loss every time
    ARead  was run.  I guess you all have plenty of RAM eh?  All
    buffers  are  now allocated in one big pool which saves some
    bytes of code and gains a little speed.

  - ARead  now uses part of it's internal version string as  the
    screen title.  This saves a whopping 14 bytes :^)


v2.0 (26/3/1998)

  - Fixed  some  nasty  Enforcer  hits,  thanks  again Nils  for
    finding  these.   They  sure were hard to track down without
    Enforcer!   Anybody  wanna  send me an old accelerator board
    with 68030 and MMU for my old trusty A2000?

  - ARead no longer uses MEMF_PUBLIC!MEMF_CLEAR when  allocating
    buffer  for textfile, just MEMF_PUBLIC.  There's no sense in
    filling  the  buffer  with  zeros when you are just going to
    fill  it  with a textfile :^)

  - Removed  several redundant references that got left  over in
    V2.0 when ARead got rewritten to be PURE.

  - Yahoo!!! Finally got ARead  well under the 3kb size.  I have
    shaved nearly 400 bytes from V2.0b

  - Began implementing conditional  assembly statements so I can
    make 68020+ versions of ARead too.

  - Fixed unreported feature that made ARead sometimes forget to
    print the last line of text from a file.

  - If  a  pubscreen  name  was  specified  at CLI/Shell  but no
    filename was specified, ARead would open it's file requester
    on the front pubscreen and then open it's window on the same
    screen  overriding  the  PUBSCREEN argument.  Fixed now  and
    the  window  and  file  requester  both  open on the correct
    screen.


v2.0b (22/3/1998) (no public release)

  - This  is a major update so ARead gets a new  version instead
    of just a revision.

  - As  mentioned  above, a major overhaul.  This was  needed to
    make  ARead  fully reentrant so it can be made resident when
    run  from  shell/cli  (requested by Nils Goers).  Thanks for
    the example resident code Nils.

  - Thought  I  had  better get rid of ARead.doc and  replace it
    with this nice guide instead.


v1.3 (6/3/1998)

  - Corrected  small feature when ARead is run from CLI  with no
    arguments.   Previously ARead would open it's file requester
    in  the  SYS:   directory.  Now ARead opens the requester in
    the current directory.


v1.2 (5/3/1998)

  - Changed  fallback  font  code  again.   Now  if  no font  is
    specified  or  if  the  specified font cannot be opened then
    ARead  will  try  to use the font of the screen it opens on.
    If  this  too fails then you get the default system font ala
    graphics library gb_DefaultFont.  (Requested by Nils Goers).

  - Changed  some dcb.b data to ds.b bss to save  some space and
    keep ARead under 4kb in size.

  - Added  code  to  formatter to make ARead replace CR and  TAB
    characters into spaces.


v1.1 (4/3/1998)

  - Added ASL FileRequest if no name  specified from shell or if
    ARead  is  not  started  from  WB  as  the default tool of a
    project.  (Requested by Nils Goers).  Thanks for the example
    ASL code Nils.

  - Added  ability to open on specified PubScreen (Requested  by
    Nils Goers).

  - Changed fallback font from topaz.font to default system font
    (Requested by Nils Goers).


v1.0 (21/2/1998)

  - first public release
@ENDNODE

